&lt;p&gt;Maven is a market-leading proprietary trading firm deploying its own capital across discretionary, systematic, and market-making strategies. Backed by deep expertise in trading, technology, and research, we are relentlessly focused on improving liquidity across global listed derivatives. Through advanced execution and pricing technologies, we improve how financial markets operate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Compliance Analyst to join our Hong Kong based Compliance team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Compliance Analyst, you will contribute to the effective operation of the firm according to its regulatory and internal policy requirements as they apply across the diverse range of trading activities carried out. You will also add value supporting this firm in achieving its forward-looking growth and development plans. In doing so, you will gain exposure to key aspects of compliance, supporting electronic options market making and multi-strategy trading (encompassing proprietary equity and bond strategies such as event trading and equity capital markets), regulatory monitoring, prudential compliance, policy implementation, and employee trading oversight.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will thrive in a fast-paced proprietary trading environment. As Maven continues to develop and to expand its business activities the complexity of the regulatory and exchange landscape, within which we operate, increases in parallel. Our aim is to ensure Compliance provides market leading support for the firm and, in doing so, ensures its safe, effective and sustainable growth and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Comprehensive training will be provided to ensure your success and ongoing development in this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Policies, Procedures, and Training Materials&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the review and update of compliance policies and procedures and assist with the drafting and maintenance of training materials and employee guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Internal Reporting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the compilation and coordination of internal compliance reports, including quarterly compliance reports and other periodic disclosures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wall-crossing &amp;amp; Restricted List Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the safe and effective operation of Maven’s wall-crossing processes and assist with maintaining restricted lists and watch lists. Work directly with our trading business units to support the implementation of effective information barriers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Compliance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Maven’s extensive operational compliance framework, contributing to processes such as those related to personal account dealing. Escalate potential compliance issues and contribute to documentation and reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Regulatory Reporting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the preparation and validation of regulatory filings required under UK, EU, US, and other relevant regimes; work with the team to ensure timely and accurate submissions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;External Document Requests &amp;amp; Regulatory Enquiries&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with responding to requests from regulators and counterparties, including regulatory questionnaires and due diligence enquiries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Training &amp;amp; Attestation Administration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate the tracking and completion of mandatory compliance training and attestations across the firm.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advising Trading Desks&l

&lt;p&gt;Thank you for your interest in Maven!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please use this link to register your interest in our roles and be notified when applications open.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the meantime, please check out our website and social media to stay up to date with what&#39;s happening at Maven!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to reviewing your application soon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;End User Support Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Core Infrastructure team&lt;/strong&gt; is a diverse group of technologists, who focus on continuously improving the end-to-end resiliency, scalability, visibility, usability, and supportability of Maven&#39;s technology systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The End User Support team&lt;/strong&gt; is responsible for the user experience at Maven, managing technology and facilities to help our users achieve greater productivity. To achieve these goals, the team owns responsibility for the office and desktop environment, video conferencing systems, telephony, and more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The End User Support Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; ensures that Maven’s employees have everything they need to be successful and productive on their desk and at their fingertips. You will take the lead on building efficient desk configurations, moving employees, setting up new desktops, and helping people get the most out of Maven’s technology tools. This position forms the first line of support for IT problems and requests, coordinating with the other members of the Core Infrastructure and development teams as necessary to resolve end users requests and keep our employees productive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the installation and configuration of desktop computing solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Application Management including configuration and version control.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide Escalation level support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate technology setups for new employees and role changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain AV and video conferencing technology throughout the office.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow and update procedural documentation e.g. Linux deployment, user onboarding.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and update the inventory of office IT equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure telephones, printers, and other common office technology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with external vendors and suppliers as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we’re looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting Windows and Linux desktop environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience with Ubuntu, including a full rollout of managed devices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Ubuntu Landscape for management, patching automation, auditing, and access management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Linux in an Active Directory integrated environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of deployment platforms such as PDQ, SCCM, MDT, Intune.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of Scripting languages such as PowerShell or Python.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with automation tools like Ansible for configuration management and application deployment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with CI/CD tools, particularly Jenkins, for automating build, test, and deployment processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with Git for version control.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting Microsoft Office productivity software, particularly Excel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to multitask and prioritize efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of basic networking concepts: DHCP, DNS, cabling standards, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outstanding attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Desire to learn new skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent customer support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with virtual desktops (Omnissa Horizon preferred) is a big plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE CAN OFFER YOU&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive compensation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Group Pension plan&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual discretionary bonus&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fully catered breakfast, lunch and snacks.&amp;nb

&lt;p&gt;Maven is a market-leading proprietary trading firm deploying its own capital across discretionary, systematic, and market-making strategies. Backed by deep expertise in trading, technology, and research, we are relentlessly focused on improving liquidity across global listed derivatives. Through advanced execution and pricing technologies, we improve how financial markets operate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE: &lt;/strong&gt;We are looking for an ambitious and proactive European Single Stock Options Market Maker with a proven profit / risk management history to be a part of our equity options market making desk. The eligible candidate has extensive experience trading single stocks options on multiple European exchanges as well as the ability and leadership skills to build out expanding desks.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Day-to-day responsibility of trading and managing a part of the single stocks options book&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rigorous risk management and compliance with regulatory rules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improving option pricing and trading strategies through close collaboration with a team of fundamental stock analysts&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designing, implementing and improving strategies through data&amp;nbsp; analysis, prototyping and collaboration with developers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Driving pricing and execution improvements through combining systematic and quantitative skills with product knowledge&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CANDIDATE SPECIFICATIONS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 3 years experience trading European single stock options in a market making role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Successful track record of proven P&amp;amp;L and market share&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good understanding of the market structure of European single stock options&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outstanding numerical, analytical skills and excellent attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with automated options trading strategies and a proactive interest in their development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to take a high level of responsibility in an expanding, highly successful firm&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embodiment of Maven’s core values: Integrity and fairness, market leading, creativity, individual and collective success, discipline and accountability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in programming is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maven is a market-leading proprietary trading firm deploying its own capital across discretionary, systematic, and market-making strategies. Backed by deep expertise in trading, technology, and research, we are relentlessly focused on improving liquidity across global listed derivatives. Through advanced execution and pricing technologies, we improve how financial markets operate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;As a Group Accountant, you’ll join a high-performing UK-based finance team within a fast-paced trading organisation. This is a key control and reporting role with excellent exposure to how the business operates end-to-end. You’ll take ownership of balance sheet integrity across a portfolio of&amp;nbsp;group entities, support the close process, and play a key role in delivering statutory reporting&amp;nbsp;(including consolidated accounts). You’ll partner with teams across the firm to strengthen controls,&amp;nbsp;improve processes, and support high-impact finance projects&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the close timetable, coordinating dependencies and act as a key point of contact for stakeholders across Finance and the wider business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and review journal entries, including accruals, prepayments, intercompany, and other complex postings as required, ensuring appropriate supporting documentation and audit trail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and maintain robust balance sheet reconciliations, ensuring reconciling items are identified, supported, and cleared on a timely basis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the preparation, review, and audit of statutory financial statements for group entities, including consolidated group accounts, and act as a primary contact for auditors on your areas of ownership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and enhance accounting policies and technical documentation, particularly for complex, judgemental, or higher-risk transactions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay up to date with IFRS developments, assessing impact and supporting implementation across the group&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the completion and submission of regulatory returns where applicable, while keeping up to date with the evolving regulatory landscape, assessing potential impacts on the business, and supporting any required changes to reporting processes or controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support tax compliance and reporting by providing accurate schedules, reconciliations, and supporting documentation to internal stakeholders and/or external tax advisers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead automation and the effective utilisation of AI tools to improve reporting quality, streamline reconciliations, support variance analysis and commentary, and increase efficiency—while ensuring appropriate review and controls are maintained&lt;/li&gt;
