&lt;li

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Maven is a market-leading proprietary trading firm deploying its own capital across discretionary, systematic, and market-making strategies. Backed by deep expertise in trading, technology, and research, we are relentlessly focused on improving liquidity across global listed derivatives. Through advanced execution and pricing technologies, we improve how financial markets operate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Head of Market Data is responsible for the development and execution of Maven&#39;s market data strategy, requirements, and vendor negotiations. Working with the wider business stakeholders, the Head of Market Data will manage all commercial, strategic, and administrative aspects of the market data lifecycle, collaborating closely with technology counterparts who are responsible for data delivery and any technical requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position requires a keen understanding of the global market data industry, including market data policies, business models, and pricing, as well as a solid understanding of Maven&#39;s strategy and objectives as far as they relate to market data. The role will require a strong balance of strategic vision, commercial outlook, and operational expertise to provide the most optimum platform for growth with minimal risk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position will sit in London, reporting into the Chief Legal Officer and working closely with business and technology stakeholders. It is a full-time permanent role and remuneration comprises an annual base salary depending on experience plus a discretionary bonus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hybrid working:&lt;/strong&gt; 4 days a week in the office&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Strategy &amp;amp; Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development and ownership of Maven&#39;s overarching Market Data Strategy, including a roadmap for data sourcing, cost management, vendor diversification, and alignment with business growth objectives;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding the distinct market data requirements across Maven&#39;s business areas, including discretionary trading, systematic/quantitative trading, and options market making;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Defining and tracking KPIs for the market data function, reporting progress to senior management;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acting as Maven&#39;s subject matter expert and internal advisor on all market data matters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Process Improvement &amp;amp; Operational Excellence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and optimisation of existing market data processes, workflows, and governance frameworks, identifying inefficiencies and implementing improvements;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete management of monthly data reporting, annual licensing, and exchange audits, collaborating with technology to achieve automation where possible;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Management of Maven&#39;s data catalogue, raising its profile with business users as a tool to review available data sets;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding technical, industry, regulatory, trading, and business operations detail and its impact to support business decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creation of a data inventory for use by Maven staff, indexing all data usage across the business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
