&lt;p&gt;Maven is a market-leading proprietary trading firm deploying its own capital across discretionary, systematic, and market-making strategies. Backed by deep expertise in trading, technology, and research, we are relentlessly focused on improving liquidity across global listed derivatives. Through advanced execution and pricing technologies, we improve how financial markets operate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Market Data Manager is responsible for the operational, technological, and AI-driven engine of Maven&#39;s Market Data function across all regions and business lines. Reporting to the Head of Market Data, the individual will deliver against Maven&#39;s Market Data strategy with a particular focus on AI-enabled vendor analytics, contract digestion, entitlement audit, and the build-out of the firm&#39;s data inventory and reporting infrastructure. This position requires a strong commercial and operational grounding across the breadth of market data (exchange, alternative, and fundamental) alongside a demonstrable track record of using LLMs, automation, and lightweight Python to replace manual workflows. The role will partner closely with the Head of Vendor Strategy on commercial strategy, vendor negotiations, and the build-out of the function, while owning the day-to-day operational running of the team. The successful candidate will be hands-on, comfortable doing the work themselves rather than delegating it, and will demonstrate strong commercial instinct alongside technical fluency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position will sit in London, working closely with business and technology stakeholders globally. The role will manage Maven&#39;s Data Licensing Administrator and partner closely with the procurement team on the contract repository, vendor analytics, and inventory infrastructure. The operational and AI capability of this role is expected to be leveraged across Maven&#39;s Vendor Strategy, Finance and Legal functions in addition to Market Data. It is a full-time permanent role and remuneration comprises an annual base salary depending on experience plus a discretionary bonus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hybrid working: &lt;/strong&gt;4 days a week in the office&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI, Automation &amp;amp; Operational Tooling&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Ownership of the AI and automation roadmap for the Market Data function, deciding what to build, what to buy, and what to outsource;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Daily use of LLMs and AI tooling for vendor analysis, contract digestion, usage analytics, and entitlement audit, with a track record of replacing manual workflows with AI-augmented equivalents;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Use of internal tooling in Python (usage dashboards, automated entitlement reconciliations, simple AI integrations), working adjacent to engineering rather than as engineering;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Automation of monthly reporting, exchange audit workflows, and other repetitive tasks across the Market Data function;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Ownership of MD data ingestion into Maven&#39;s central data team infrastructure, enabling easy access and inventory management firmwide.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vendor Analytics &amp;amp; Commercial Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Day-to-day ownership of vendor analytics: usage, ROI, redundancy, and renewal forecasting across the full Market Data vendor portfolio;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Support on vendor negotiations, renewal strategy, and RFP processes with major data and exchange vendors (e.g., Bloomberg, LSE/Refinitiv, ICE, CME);&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Building of forecast and ROI models to optimise spend and inform future Opex planning;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li

