&lt;p&gt;Maven is a market-leading proprietary trading firm deploying its own capital across discretionary, systematic, and market-making strategies. Backed by deep expertise in trading, technology, and research, we are relentlessly focused on improving liquidity across global listed derivatives. Through advanced execution and pricing technologies, we improve how financial markets operate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OVERVIEW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a global firm with trading strategies that operate worldwide, we want to create and maintain a globally consistent platform, removing as much work as possible from our trading and development teams when building, developing and running their applications. We are looking for an experienced technical operations specialist, DevOps engineer, or Platform Engineer to join a small existing team and help shape this vision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The individual will have operational responsibility for several production trading and research environments and will need to understand how our systems work throughout the trading lifecycle, from the front to the back office. The role will require close collaboration with traders, developers, quant researchers, data engineers, and infrastructure teams to ensure our production systems are well-understood and properly configured. The individual will also be expected to advocate for operational efficiency and continuous improvement across all deployment aspects, as well as troubleshooting, monitoring, automation, and resiliency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are just at the beginning of an exciting transformation project to consolidate and standardise how we run and research our applications inside Maven, and the individual will have the opportunity to shape the future of this platform&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is based in London, but the team will be globally distributed. Communication skills, a pragmatic approach to problem-solving under time pressure, and a positive mindset are essential for success in this role. Candidates will likely have at least 2+ years of experience in a similar position. In particular, we are looking for:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a highly motivated individual with creative problem-solving skills;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a self-starter attitude and proactive problem ownership mindset;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to prioritise effectively whilst keeping longer-term objectives in mind;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an opportunity for someone who wants to have a meaningful impact within Maven to help define and shape a role that uniquely interfaces with all other functions within the firm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MUST HAVE&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building systems with a constant focus on reliability, scalability, and maintainability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designing and programming in a variety of languages and technologies.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working on legacy code as well as green field development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Initiative driving projects to completion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learning and promoting new technologies with a focus on best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building and automating various operations tasks using scripting languages such as Python, including configuration checks, system health monitoring, alerting, reliability report generation, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to adapt to steep learning curves and navigate large volumes of information&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NICE TO HAVE&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Multiple years of server-side development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to Kubernetes, Docker, Linux, Kafka, Prometheus, and other modern deployment tooling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working closely with both traders and automated strategies in a similar front-office environment to identify and implement operational improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&

&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a portfolio manager with a deep understanding of a particular inefficiency they attempt to capture. They will have been heavily involved in the research of the strategy as well as its implementation, and are able to develop new strategies from idea to implementation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In addition, the PM will have a solid understanding of the dynamics of markets, and use these dynamics to display a qualitative appreciation of when their strategy performs well and poorly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Offices in both London and Monaco.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years experience as a PM, or 4-5 years as an assistant PM;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Realised Sharpe &amp;gt;2.5;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Display track record of strategy;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of strategy;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong coding skills;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong researching skills;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Masters or PHD in scientific subject.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-Onsite&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Maven is a proprietary trading organisation formed in 2011, that has offices in London, Amsterdam, Hong Kong, New York and Sydney&lt;/p&gt;
