&lt;li&gt;Academic degree in applied mathematics, computer science, statistics engineering or physics. PhD or any other track record in conducting independent research.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 3+ years of experience in the financial industry, particularly electronic options trading.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to research advanced algorithms, develop predictive models and verify complex hypotheses using large datasets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactive interest in improving existing trading strategies and identifying new opportunities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative bridge between developers, and traders who aligns technical work with commercial impact and the broader strategic vision, and a real team player with other quants in the team.&lt;/li&gt;
